## Tier B — harness registration & D-anchor hook-env gate (2026-07-01)

Probe: one isolation:worktree general-purpose subagent (ac800f3cb64e85f0), via
the Agent tool. Its worktree: .worktrees/agent-ac800f3cb64e85f03,
git-common-dir=/workspace/doctrine/.git (a genuine linked worktree of THIS repo).

FINDING B-reg (registration): the subagent's Write to /tmp/va1-escape-probe.txt
SUCCEEDED (not denied); bash ran unwrapped. ⇒ the freshly-installed plugin
PreToolUse hook is NOT live in this already-running session. Confirms
NO-HOT-RELOAD: the installed hook needs /reload-plugins or a session restart to
register (matches the runbook + PHASE-01, which needed a restart). Expected;
in-session live registration is structurally unreachable.

FINDING B-anchor (the D-anchor EMPIRICAL GATE — CAUTION, MISMEASURE):
the subagent reported CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR=[] (empty) — BUT it read its own
TOOL-EXEC env, NOT the hook-process env. Per docs/claude/hooks.md:366 Claude Code
exports CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR into the *hook* spawned-process env (a distinct
process); hooks.md:462 lists hooks/stdio-MCP/LSP as where it is set — the
subagent's Bash tool is none of these. So the empty tool-env value is NOT
evidence the hook lacks the anchor. The gate remains OPEN: it requires the HOOK
process's own env, which needs a LIVE-registered hook.

REMAINING LIVE GATE (needs /reload-plugins or restart, then re-probe):
Re-express against the REGISTERED hook with a worktree subagent battery:
  L1 (Bash wall):   subagent runs `echo x` → expect it to run but CONFINED
                    (bwrap-wrapped via updatedInput). Confirms Bash wall live.
  L2 (D-ANCHOR DISCRIMINATOR): subagent writes a file INSIDE its worktree →
                    ALLOWED  ⇒ CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR present in hook env ⇒ D-anchor
                                CONFIRMED, dispatch works. VA-1 GREEN.
                    DENIED "cwd-not-a-worktree" ⇒ anchor ABSENT in hook env ⇒
                                over-confinement (all worker writes/bash deny) ⇒
                                /consult + fallback (is_linked_worktree-only),
                                NOT a silent change (per notes EMPIRICAL GATE).
  L3 (Edit|Write wall): subagent writes to /tmp (escape) → expect DENY. Confirms
                    the write wall live.
L2 is the sole discriminator: only the anchor-present path allows an in-worktree
write; both anchor-absent and escape deny.

STATUS: Tier A GREEN (installed exec correct end-to-end). Registration + D-anchor
